Revised workflow for writing-skill review:

  1. You share URLs or content (one or many, across messages)
  2. You signal "done sharing" when ready for analysis
  3. Iterate below steps until you are satisfied with the plan
  4. I audit writing-skills and any new planned to be created or updated skills against all collected best practices
  5. I delta-check — filter out what's already covered vs genuinely missing/outdated
  6. I classify each finding by scope: project-only, hub, or both
  7. I brainstorm — trade-offs, priorities, alternatives
  8. I draft an implementation plan
  9. I self-audit the plan for gaps and edge cases
  10. I revise plan to close gaps
  11. audit plan against the original URL and see if any gaps or edge case still remain
  12. if yes then go to step 3 and repeat
  13. You approve before I implement

